      "oldText": "The issued permit does not authorize an alternate operating scenario that bypasses TREA 2 for STRU 11 maintenance.",
      "newText": "5.46.2 STRU 11 Alternate Operating Scenario 2-Emissions are vented directly from EQUIs 18, 191, and 243 out to atmosphere while TREA 2 is undergoing maintenance. All other units are not allowed to operate under AOS 2. When operating under AOS 2, the Permittee may vent emissions from EQUIs 18, 191, and 243 out to atmosphere and bypass having those emissions be controlled by a baghouse that meets the requirements of TREA 2. This operating scenario only applies during times that TREA 2 is undergoing maintenance. [ Minn. R. 7007.0800, subp. 11, Minn. R. 7007.0800, subp. 2(A) & (B), Minn. R. 7009.0020-7009.0090, Minn. Stat. 116.07, subd. 4a(a), Title I Condition: Avoid major source under 40 CFR 52.21(b)(1)(i) and Minn. R. 7007.3000]",
      "changeType": "Addition",
      "initialAnalysis": "The draft adds AOS 2 for STRU 11 and allows EQUIs 18, 191, and 243 to vent directly to atmosphere while TREA 2 is undergoing maintenance. That is one of the most substantive changes in the draft because it authorizes a direct-vent operating mode that the issued permit did not clearly allow. Even though the scenario is limited to maintenance, it changes both control strategy and compliance posture.",
      "regulatoryImpact": "This is a new permit authorization affecting when control equipment must operate and when bypassed emissions are permissible. It should be treated as a material change in permit scope and enforceability.",
      "operationalImpact": "The facility gains maintenance flexibility, but it must manage the bypass carefully because the scenario will likely draw scrutiny from both the agency and client stakeholders.",
      "riskLevel": "High",
      "recommendedFollowUp": "Flag for client discussion and verify the application, emissions calculations, and modeled assumptions fully support this bypass scenario.",
