      "id": "PC-024",
      "oldSection": "5.59.27-5.59.28",
      "newSection": "5.59.27-5.59.28",
      "subjectPrimary": "CAM",
      "subjectSecondary": "Recordkeeping",
      "oldText": "5.59.27 Recordkeeping of Recirculating Scrubber Water FlowRate: At least once during every 24-hour period, the Permittee shall record the time and date of Recirculating Scrubber water flowrate reading for the applicable Operating Scenarios, and whether or not the observed value was within the range specified in this permit. Recorded values outside any range specified in this permit are considered Deviations as defined by Minn. R. 7007.0100, subp. 8a and are considered excursions as defined by 40 CFR 64.1. [40 CFR 64.9(b), Minn. R. 7007.0800, subp. 11, Minn. R. 7007.0800, subps. 4-5, Minn. R. 7017.0200, Title I Condition: Avoid major source under 40 CFR 52.21(b)(1)(i) and Minn. R. 7007.3000, Title I Condition: Avoid major source under 40 CFR 63.2]\n\n5.59.28 Recordkeeping of ABS Additive Liquid Flow Rate: At least once during every 24-hour period, the Permittee shall record the time and date of ABS Additive Liquid FlowRate reading for the applicable Operating Scenarios, and whether or not the observed value was within the range specified in this permit. Recorded values outside any range specified in this permit are considered Deviations as defined by Minn. R. 7007.0100, subp. 8a and are considered excursions as defined by 40 CFR 64.1. [40 CFR 64.9(b), Minn. R. 7007.0800, subp. 11, Minn. R. 7007.0800, subps. 4-5, Minn. R. 7017.0200, Title I Condition: Avoid major source under 40 CFR 52.21(b)(1)(i) and Minn. R. 7007.3000, Title I Condition: Avoid major source under 40 CFR 63.2]",
